answerText: isomorphic [or word forms][10] The graph isomorphism problem is probably the strongest candidate for being in this complexity class. As a converse of Ladner's theorem, a proof that this class is non-empty would demonstrate that P does not equal NP.

question: Question:  [10] Name this property, which a pair of graphs has if there exists an edge-preserving bijection between their vertices. More generally, a pair of objects has this property if there is an invertible homomorphism between them.
